The '''Federal Rules of Evidence''' are the ground rules for trials in the United States federal court system. This text presents the rules in order, along with examples and commentary on key points of the law of evidence. __NOTOC__ __NOEDITSECTION__ ==Table of contents== [[File:Great Seal of the United States (obverse).svg|right|319px]] #[[/Introduction/]] - ''Scope - Mechanics'' #[[/Judicial Notice/]] #[[/Presumptions in Civil Actions/]] - ''Burden of going forward - Burden of persuasion'' #[[/Relevancy/]] - ''Unfair prejudice - Character evidence - Habit - Policy exclusions - Sex offenses'' #[[/Privileges/]] #[[/Witnesses/]] - ''Competency - Credibility - Impeachment'' #[[/Opinions/]] - ''Lay opinions - Expert opinions'' #[[/Hearsay/]] - ''Rule - Confrontation Clause - Exceptions'' #[[/Authentication/]] #[[/Documents/]] #[[/Miscellaneous Rules/]]
