The [[w:JavaServer Pages|JavaServer Pages]] is a technology for inserting dynamic content into a [[HTML Programming|HTML]] or [[XML]] page using a Java servlet container. In other word, instead of sending HTML pages to web clients that are always the same for every one, you can send HTML pages that can be different for each client and each time they recieve it (using database data for instance). To explain it, let's have a simple HTML page on a web server. The data flow is simple. To put it simple, the client requests a HTML page by sending the page URL and the server returns the given HTML page:

